Author Name: **Krzysztof Jankowski**
Original Redmine Message: 1093 from https://www.veripool.org



---

Below SV code doesn't seem to compile with "verilator -sc unsized.sv" command:

```
`define DELAY #1

module test1(
  input  logic      clock;
  input  logic      reset;
  input  logic[7:0] datai;
  output logic[7:0] datao;
);

always_ff @(posedge clock)
begin
  if (reset == 1'b0)
     datao <= `DELAY '0;  // unsized SV integer (truncated), doesn't compile
     //datao <= `DELAY 0;   // 32-bit integer (truncated), this does compile
  else
     datao <= `DELAY datai;
end

endmodule

```

Error message:
%Error: unsized.sv:13: syntax error, unexpected ';', expecting TYPE-IDENTIFIER

I've tried with all available --default-language options and none of them worked, however the pre-processing only (-E option) works just fine. I'm just starting my SV adventure, and above was found by trying to re-compile a large existing SV project which I can't modify.
I think the issue is around the unsized SV integers which are described for example here:
http://www.asic-world.com/systemverilog/literal_values1.html

